# Gcore Video Player SDK — General Rules

Package: `@gcorevideo/player` | Built on Clappr | TypeScript | Plugin-based

## Critical integration patterns

Plugin registration must precede player instantiation — always:
```ts
Player.registerPlugin(MediaControl)   // ← before new Player()
Player.registerPlugin(SourceController)
const player = new Player({ sources: [...] })
```

Always pair autoPlay with mute:
```ts
new Player({ autoPlay: true, mute: true, sources: [...] })
```

Always destroy on component cleanup:
```ts
return () => player.destroy()   // React
onUnmounted(() => player.destroy())  // Vue
onDestroy(() => player.destroy())    // Svelte
```

CSS is required:
```ts
import '@gcorevideo/player/dist/index.css'
```

## TypeScript

- No `any` — use `unknown` with type guards
- Public types → `packages/player/src/types.ts`
- Internal types → `packages/player/src/internal.types.ts`
- Plugin option interfaces named `[PluginName]PluginSettings`

## What NOT to do

- Do not modify Clappr core directly
- Do not use jQuery (Clappr uses Zepto `$`)
- Do not break public API backward compatibility
- Do not import `@gcorevideo/player` at SSR module level (Next.js, Nuxt)
- Do not register plugins inside React components — register once at app level
